In this gripping video, we take you back to a shocking moment in sports history that unfolded in 1994 at the Oslo athletics ground. Watch as Finnish thrower Juha Laukkanen launches his javelin, which unexpectedly veers off course and strikes a judge! The stadium falls silent as blood begins to flow, but fortunately, the judge survives this harrowing incident. Just four years later, in 1998, history repeats itself when Laukkanen's javelin strikes another judge, leading to a life-threatening situation. This video delves into these brutal moments that left an indelible mark on the world of athletics. Join us as we explore the details of these shocking events and their impact on sports safety.
